		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://boingboing.net/?p=306894</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Without <a href="http://cryptome.org">Cryptome.org</a>, there would have been no Wikileaks, though the two organizations' history and methods of operation couldn't be more different.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<img src="http://boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/nya-kick.large_.jpg" alt="nya-kick.large" width="220" height="220" class="alignright size-full wp-image-306900" />Without <a href="http://cryptome.org">Cryptome.org</a>, there would have been no Wikileaks, though the two organizations' history and methods of operation couldn't be more different. I'm pretty sure it's the oldest continuously-running website devoted to the public exposure of secret documents for the public good, and has weathered constant attack and intimidation by entities who would rather that websites like Cryptome not exist.
<p>
 The website run by John Young and Deborah Natsios <a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1874173687/cryptome-global-archives">has a kickstarter campaign</a>, and it's worth considering kicking in if radical transparency is something you support. <p><span id="more-306894"></span>





<blockquote>Cryptome publishes documents prohibited worldwide, in particular material on freedom of expression.
<p>
Cryptome has been primarily funded for 18 years by its operators with modest funding by donations for copies of its archives. Outside support would be appreciated but the site will continue in any event.
<p>
Cryptome publishes documents prohibited worldwide, in particular material on freedom of expression, privacy, cryptology, dual-use technologies, national security, intelligence, and secret governance -- open, secret and classified documents -- but not limited to those.

</blockquote>




<iframe width="680" height="510" src="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/1874173687/cryptome-global-archives/widget/video.html" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"> </iframe>]]></content:encoded>
