Edward Snowden's lawyer reports that <a href="http://world.time.com/2013/11/12/edward-snowden-is-almost-broke/">he is almost broke</a>, having spent his savings on subsistence since he went into exile; he has been relying on "some organizations and enterprising citizens" for his ongoing expenses. There doesn't appear to be an easy way to give money to Snowden himself (<a href="https://blockchain.info/address/1snowqQP5VmZgU47i5AWwz9fsgHQg94Fa">you can send BitCoins here</a>), though <a href="https://wikileaks.org/freesnowden">there's a legal defense fund</a> operated by Wikileaks.

