		<item>
		<title>Inspired by Snowden, more NSA insiders are blowing the&#160;whistle</title>
		<link>http://boingboing.net/2013/11/02/inspired-by-snowden-more-nsa.html</link>
		<comments>http://boingboing.net/2013/11/02/inspired-by-snowden-more-nsa.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 02 Nov 2013 22:01:34 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Cory Doctorow]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Post]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[happy mutants]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[nsa]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[petard]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[snowden]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[spooks]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[whistleblowers]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://boingboing.net/?p=265787</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>

Jesselyn Radack is a civil liberties attorney with the <a href="http://www.whistleblower.org/">Government Accountability Project</a> who has been in contact with Edward Snowden. In an <a href="http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2013/10/more-nsa-leakers-followed-snowdens-footsteps-whistleblower-lawyer-says/">ABC News interview</a>, she reported that other NSA insiders have been inspired by Snowden's bravery and sacrifice and have come forward with further revelations about the organization's excess, criminality and lawlessness.</p>]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>
<img src="http://boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2013/11/abcnewsindex1.jpg" class="bordered" align="right">
Jesselyn Radack is a civil liberties attorney with the <a href="http://www.whistleblower.org/">Government Accountability Project</a> who has been in contact with Edward Snowden. In an <a href="http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2013/10/more-nsa-leakers-followed-snowdens-footsteps-whistleblower-lawyer-says/">ABC News interview</a>, she reported that other NSA insiders have been inspired by Snowden's bravery and sacrifice and have come forward with further revelations about the organization's excess, criminality and lawlessness. She says that the Obama administration's war on whistleblowers has backfired, squandering the administration's credibility with its own operatives and inspiring them to speak out.

<span id="more-265787"></span>

<blockquote>
<p>


“I think the government hopes to chill speech by employees in the national security and intelligence fields, especially those at the NSA and CIA, but the unintended consequence is [that] more and more whistleblowers are coming through the doors of the Government Accountability Project (GAP),” said Jesselyn Radack, referring to the organization where she works as the National Security and Human Rights Director. “I think courage is contagious, and we see more and more people from the NSA coming through our door after Snowden made these revelations.”
<p>
Radack, an attorney who has met with and been in communication with Snowden, said “a handful” of people in the intelligence community have come forward since this summer when several major international newspapers began writing about the NSA’s classified foreign and domestic surveillance programs – stories based on thousands of secret NSA documents allegedly stolen by Snowden, a former NSA contractor.
</blockquote>

<p>
<a href="http://abcnews.go.com/blogs/headlines/2013/10/more-nsa-leakers-followed-snowdens-footsteps-whistleblower-lawyer-says/">More NSA Leakers Followed Snowden’s Footsteps, Whistleblower Lawyer Says</a> [Brian Ross and Rhonda Schwartz/ABC]
<p>
(<i>via <a href="http://nakedcapitalism.com/">Naked Capitalism</a></i>)

]]></content:encoded>
